SELECT 
    DATE_TRUNC('month', be.event_month)::DATE AS month,
    COALESCE(p.tier, 'Unknown') AS tier,
    COALESCE(c.industry, 'Unknown') AS industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT s.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(be.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT u.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM subscriptions s
INNER JOIN billing_events be ON s.subscription_id = be.subscription_id
INNER JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
WHERE ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY s.subscription_id, DATE_TRUNC('month', be.event_month) ORDER BY be.event_id) = 1
GROUP BY DATE_TRUNC('month', be.event_month)::DATE, COALESCE(p.tier, 'Unknown'), COALESCE(c.industry, 'Unknown')
ORDER BY month DESC, tier, industry;

WITH deduped_billing AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT ON (subscription_id, DATE_TRUNC('month', event_month)::DATE)
        subscription_id,
        DATE_TRUNC('month', event_month)::DATE AS event_month,
        amount
    FROM billing_events
    ORDER BY subscription_id, DATE_TRUNC('month', event_month)::DATE, event_id
),
active_subs AS (
    SELECT 
        db.event_month,
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        COALESCE(p.tier, 'Unknown') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, 'Unknown') AS industry,
        db.amount
    FROM deduped_billing db
    INNER JOIN subscriptions s ON db.subscription_id = s.subscription_id
    INNER JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
    LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
    LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
)
SELECT 
    event_month AS month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM active_subs
GROUP BY event_month, tier, industry
ORDER BY month DESC, tier, industry;
